 be developed.European Studies:1. Understanding and analytical skills regarding international issues: the ability to understand and analyze various regions of the world from different perspectives in the humanities and social sciences.2. Problem-solving skills: the ability to proactively identify problems and solve them based on appropriate methods.3. Intercultural understanding and multicultural coexistence: the ability to be sensitive to different cultures and to coexist with diverse cultures."], "学生による授業評価の方法Course Evaluation by Students2": ["Direct feedback and feedback through LUNA"], "成績評価Grading0": ["種別　Type備考　Note", "割合　Percentage", "評価基準等　Grading Criteria etc."], "成績評価Grading1": ["その他／Others (99)", "100 %", "See below"], "成績評価Grading2": ["備考　Note 12 Mini tests at the end of each face-to-face class (80%) and a small report about the on-demand classes (20%). For getting the credits at least 7 Mini tests have to be handed in"], "更新日時/Date of Update0": ["2026年02月19日 18時17分04秒"], "項番No.0": [], "項番No.1": ["2026年度", "秋学期／Fall", "水曜２時限／Wednesday 2", "秋学期／Fall", "Ｇ－ＩＳ１０８"]}, "campas": 0, "name": "【430】Economic History of the European Union／Economic History of the European Union [EN]", "管理部署": 10, "単位数": 2, "担当者": "ブングシェ　Ｈ．Ｒ．（BUNGSCHE HOLGER ROBERT） ", "履修基準年度": "２年", "履修登録方法": "本登録", "開講期": 2, "時限1": 15, "時限1_term": 1, "評価1": 6, "成績評価備考": "備考　Note\n12 Mini tests at the end of each face-to-face class (80%) and a small report about the on-demand classes (20%). For getting the credits at least 7 Mini tests have to be handed in"}